  "prompt": "How do I remove another Google account from my Android?",
  "response": "To remove another Google account from your Android device, follow these steps:\n\n---\n\n### **Steps to Remove a Google Account:**\n1. **Open Settings**:\n   - Swipe down from the top of the screen and tap the gear icon \u2699\ufe0f (Settings).\n\n2. **Go to Accounts**:\n   - Scroll down and tap **Accounts** (or **Passwords & Accounts**, depending on your device).\n\n3. **Select the Google Account**:\n   - Tap the Google account you want to remove.\n\n4. **Remove the Account**:\n   - Tap **Remove Account** (or **Delete Account**).\n   - Confirm by tapping **Remove Account** again.\n\n---\n\n### **What Happens When You Remove a Google Account?**\n- You will no longer have access to Gmail, Google Drive, and other Google services associated with that account on your device.\n \u00a9- Downloaded apps and data linked to that account may no longer work.\n- Contacts, calendar events, and other synced data from that account will be removed from your device.\n\n---\n\n### **Important Notes**:\n- If this is the only Google account on your device, you may not be able to remove it entirely without resetting your device.\n- Removing a Google account does not delete the account itself\u2014it only removes it from your device.\n\nLet me know if you need further assistance! \ud83d\ude0a",
